Date: 4th October 1812 - Size: Small - Location: Burgos\\Scenario
Briefing: Siege of Burgos: The Final Assault - After successfully
storming the outer enceinte on 4 October, no further progress
was made due to the weakness of the British artillery and shortage
of shot and powder. Wellington belatedly requested 24pdr naval
guns from Popham but these wouldn't arrive before the siege was
lifted. Nevertheless, continued battering and mining had created
sufficient breaches by 17 October to make it feasible to risk
launching a final assault before the siege had to be lifted.
But, eager to avoid heavy losses, Wellington sent a mere 600
men into action. Since attacking with such a small force effectively
guarantees repeating the failure of the historical assault, this
scenario will permit the British player to follow Burgoyne's
advice and commit more troops.\\Recommended Rules: Default\\Note:
This scenario is designed for an Allied player against a French
A/I
